      "comment": "IMPULSIVE REACTION (2) was in the market on debut at Warrnambool and ran very well, getting home strongly to just miss the winner over 1400m, giving every indication he'd relish 1600m here. He'll likely sit off the pace here but finds a nice race and can prove too strong late. MYKINDAKANDY (3) has been thereabouts in two runs back from a spell and should be better for them. Don't think a mile will be an issue and he draws for every chance on pace. PANDA'S SPECTRUM (7) ran a solid race on debut at Kilmore when battling away for a midfield finish. She's bred to stay and can improve off that for the good yard. OLYMPIA FIELDS (6) hasn't done a whole lot in two runs to date but could be an improver.",
